      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yup. When the GrVertexColor is constructed, we pass in a bool that indicates if we should use 8 or 16 bit colors. It the converts the passed in floats to either 8 bit unorms or half-floats, and stores the bool. We pass the same bool to GPs, and they use it to correctly configure the attribute. Then the vertex writer has a specialization for GrVertexColor that checks the bool and writes 4 or 8 bytes.",
